docs.lead_paragraph: ARLINGTON, Texas — The Los Angeles Dodgers and the Tampa Bay Rays gathered at Globe Life Field here Tuesday for the first game of the World Series, the 116th in history and the first at a neutral site. The Dodgers, who cruised to an 8-3 win, were the home team, more than 1,200 miles from their home.

headline.main: Should a Neutral-Site World Series Become Baseball’s New Normal?

docs.abstract: In 2019, Jen Wolf felt a lack of support for women like her trying to find work in professional baseball. The group chat she started has become a rare place for mentoring and understanding.
docs.snippet: In 2019, Jen Wolf felt a lack of support for women like her trying to find work in professional baseball. The group chat she started has become a rare place for mentoring and understanding.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Alyssa Nakken in July became the first woman in major league history to coach on the field, it was big news in the baseball world. But it was a particularly extraordinary development in one small corner of the industry: a text message group featuring dozens of women working in professional baseball.

headline.main: ‘They Just Get It’: How Women in M.L.B. Found Support in a Group Text
headline.print_headline: A Field Where Women Lift Women
